# Day 22 – AWS WAF & Shield Security Hardening

## Goal
Protect applications from malicious traffic and DDoS attacks.

## Steps
- Enabled AWS WAF on ALB.
- Created rules for IP blocking and SQL injection.
- Verified Shield Standard protection.
- Tested blocked requests.
- Documented rules and Shield setup.

## Lessons Learned
- WAF filters malicious traffic before it hits servers.
- Shield defends against DDoS automatically.
- Combining WAF + Shield = strong security posture.

